
A:
	I can't believe you threw that ball over the fence. Now you're going to have to go into that dark, scary, spooky forest all by yourself!

B:
	I'm not afraid! I'm not a big baby like you!

A:
	Your Highness is provided for. I'm not.

B:
	Then that should make you braver, having to provide for yourself.

A:
	Hurry up! You're making me worried. [hears scream] What was that? Hold on!

B:
	It came from the forest! We have to go see what happened.

A:
	How extraordinary! (Rising.) Well: shall we run away?

B:
	Run away? No! What if someone needs help?

A:
	It hurts so much, make it stop!

B:
	You cut yourself on the fence!

A:
	[_Takes a large loaf of bread from a drawer and cuts some slices._] An'
Juste gets forty crowns a year from the Schulze's an'....

B:
	Oh my god you're losing too much blood

A:
	Be quiet. 

B:
	no! You're hallucinating or something!

A:
	What marriage?

B:
	We need to get you to a hospital.
